    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_33_2_1811_04_27_page01.jpg"/>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>  
                        <date when="1811-04-27">April 27<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> . 1811</date>
                        <note>48</note>
                    </dateline></opener>
                      
                <p>
                    I have been balancing this great<lb/>
                    while between the fear of taking<lb/>
                    up your time with my thanks,<lb/>
                    and my earnest desire, that you<lb/>
                    should not think me ungrateful<lb/>
                    - and at last I can resist no <choice><orig>long-<lb/>
                    -er</orig><reg>longer</reg></choice> my wish to thank you, &amp;<lb/>
                    to assure you, that I know fully<lb/>
                    the value of your time  &amp; <choice><orig>consequent-<lb/>
                    ly</orig><reg>consequently</reg></choice> the value of your kindness in<lb/>
                    writing to me in the very midst<lb/>
                    of preparing your work for the press<lb/>
                    - I wish I could convey to your<lb/>
                    mind an idea of the pleasure<lb/>
                    your letter gave me,-without <choice><orig>trou-<lb/>
                    -bling</orig><reg>troubling</reg></choice> you to read this note for I am<lb/>
                    dreadfully afraid that (notwithstanding<lb/>
                    your politeness about le timbre <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE"><choice><orig>d'Edge-<lb/>
                    worthtown</orig><reg>d'Edgeworthtown</reg></choice></placeName>) the sight of it should be<lb/>
                    <del>hateful</del> disagreeable to you - And<lb/>
                    
                    <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_33_2_1811_04_27_page02.jpg"/>
                    that you should <hi rend="underline">think</hi> what I hear<lb/>
                    my <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">father</persName> <hi rend="underline">say</hi> so often when he is<lb/>
                    troubled with notes &amp; letters<lb/></p>
                    <p>
                    "Another note! Another letter!<lb/>
                    "and must I read &amp; must I answer it!"<lb/></p>
                    <p>
                    Now I will relieve you from<lb/>
                    half the evil: You <hi rend="underline">need</hi> not answer<lb/>
                    this till you hear from my <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">father</persName> -<lb/>
                    - He, who is 100,000,000,000,000,000<lb/>
                    more prudent than I am, <hi rend="underline">will</hi> not write<lb/>
                    to you till the time when you are to be at<lb/>
                    leisure - In the mean time, you will<lb/>
                    please not to take advantage of his <choice><orig>for-<lb/>
                    -bearance</orig><reg>forbearance</reg></choice> by entering into any <choice><orig>engage-<lb/>
                    ments</orig><reg>engagements</reg></choice> for your summer <hi rend="underline">vacation</hi> -<lb/>
                    Remember you have <hi rend="underline">promised</hi><lb/>
                    to come to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworth-Town</placeName> &amp; you are<lb/>
                    hereby to take notice that my <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">father</persName><lb/>
                    depends upon this promise &amp; upon<lb/>
                    your wish to fulfil it - You have told us<lb/>
                    that you shall be at liberty in June -<lb/></p>
                    <p>
                    Adieu, - I wish you well through<lb/>
                    the purgatory of authors as some one has<lb/>
                    
                    <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_33_2_1811_04_27_page03.jpg"/>
                    called the correction of the press - and I wish<lb/>
                    <add>you</add> again in their heaven - original<lb/>
                    composition - But why why do you<lb/>
                    write for <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BentJ1">Bentham</persName> &amp; not for yourself?<lb/>
                    I never shall cease to torment you<lb/>
                    with the repetition of this question<lb/>
                    till you give me a satisfactory answer<lb/>
                    - and that you can never do -<lb/></p>
                    <p>
                    I do not think you have a friend<lb/>
                    in the world who wishes more eagerly<lb/>
                    to see your new work or who is more<lb/>
                    confident of its value &amp; anxious for<lb/>
                    its success than I am - yes I will<lb/>
                    allow my <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">father</persName> <add>is</add> - but no one else<lb/></p>
                    <closer>
                    Your obliged &amp; grateful<lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName> .<lb/></closer>
                    <postscript><p>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeC1">Sneyd</persName> who is grateful to you also<lb/>
                    has just made his first <hi rend="underline">circuit</hi><lb/>
                    (do you know that term) under the<lb/>
                    most favorable auspices.-<lb/>
                    With our <hi rend="underline">Solicitor-General</hi> who is<lb/>
                    only to be surpassed by yours.<lb/></p></postscript>
                
                   <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_33_2_1811_04_27_page04.jpg"/>
                    <closer><address>
                    <addrLine>To</addrLine>
                    <addrLine><persName ref="./Personography.xml#DumoE1">E. Dumont Esq<hi rend="superscript">re</hi></persName> .</addrLine>
                    </address></closer>
                  
                   
                
                   
                
            </div>
